    "created_at": "2025-12-17T13:58:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-12-17T13:58:22Z",
    "body": "I also suspect macOS 26.2 did something, as I've had `cmd_duration` without issue until I upgraded macOS:\n\n```toml\n[cmd_duration]\nshow_milliseconds = true\nformat = \" in $duration \"\nstyle = \"bg:lavender\"\ndisabled = false\nshow_notifications = true\nmin_time_to_notify = 45000\n```\n\nConfirm: The 45s threshold does consistently explain when I need the extra `Ctrl+C`:\n\n<img width=\"530\" height=\"209\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3c10fa04-9392-44f2-855a-5fea3c3e36dc\" />\n\nConfirm: disabling the macOS notification seems to fix it:\n\n<img width=\"525\" height=\"412\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/29570f49-184d-4562-afd0-ceb00be2649a\" />\n\nThanks @kofany for this! 🙏 ",
    "author_association": "NONE",
